TO RUN LAMBDA USING DOCKER

docker run --rm -v "$PWD":/var/task lambci/lambda:go1.x my_handler '{"some": "event"}'


BUILD DOCKER FILE AND RUN IT... (json string is an example...)

COMMAND TO COMPILE THE APP FOR LINUX ENV (LAMBDA/LAMBDA DOCKER) + ZIP IT + RUN IT IN CONTAINER....
GOOS=linux go build githubparser && \
rm -f githubparser.zip && \
zip githubparser.zip githubparser && \
docker run --rm -v "$PWD":/var/task lambci/lambda:go1.x githubparser '{"ID": "fd"}'